1. *Sporo* vozimo zbog gužve na putu. (We're driving *slowly* because of the traffic.)
2. Nisam spremna da idem *sporim* tempom. (I'm not ready to go at a *slow* pace.)
3. Imamo *sporu* internet vezu danas. (We have a *slow* internet connection today.)
4. U ovoj trci, on je bio naj *sporiji*. (In this race, he was the *slowest*.)
5. Moramo biti *sporiji* u donošenju odluka. (We need to be *slower* in making decisions.)
6. Ona *sporo* jede jer uživa u hrani. (She eats *slowly* because she enjoys the food.)
7. *Sporo* se kreće zbog povrede noge. (He's moving *slowly* due to a leg injury.)
8. Deca su *spora* jutrom dok ne popiju čaj. (The children are *slow* in the morning until they have tea.)
9. *Sporo* sagorevaju ugljeni hidrati u telu. (Carbohydrates burn *slowly* in the body.)
10. U ovoj oblasti, privreda se razvija *sporo*. (In this area, the economy is developing *slowly*.)

Note: In Serbian, "sporo" can mean "slow" or "slowly" depending on its position in the sentence. Additionally, its form can change depending on the gender and number of the noun it modifies.